# .dockerignore — Controls the build context size sent by `docker build` to the daemon
#
# Dockerfile currently only requires the following paths:
#   - CMakeLists.txt
#   - src/
#   - third/           (source code only, no .git)
#   - test/interop/
#
# The repository contains a large amount of build artifacts, backups, logs, and git metadata, totaling > 5 GB, which must be excluded.
# This file takes effect every time `docker compose build` is run; please add a line here when adding new build directories or large files.

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Version control metadata (top-level repository + all submodules/vendored libraries)
# Note that third/boringssl/.git alone takes ~320 MB
# ------------------------------------------------------------
**/.git
**/.gitignore
**/.gitattributes
**/.gitmodules
.github/

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Local build directories / backups / temporary artifacts
# These make up the largest portion of the context, ranging from hundreds of MBs to 2.5 GB per item
# ------------------------------------------------------------
build
build/
build-*/
build_*/
cmake-build-*/
out/
*.bak.*/
*.bak

# Build artifact files
*.o
*.obj
*.a
*.so
*.so.*
*.dylib
*.dll
*.exe
*.lib
*.pdb
CMakeCache.txt
CMakeFiles/
cmake_install.cmake
compile_commands.json

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Test / runtime outputs (logs, downloaded files, qlog, etc., single files can be tens of MBs)
# ------------------------------------------------------------
test/interop/logs/
test/interop/downloads/
test/interop/www/
test/interop/certs/*.bak.*
test/perf/results/
test/perf/logs/
**/*.qlog
**/*.pcap
**/*.pcapng
**/*.keys
**/*.keylog

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Archives / Large objects
# ------------------------------------------------------------
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.tgz
*.tar.bz2
*.tar.xz
*.zip
*.7z
*.rar

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# IDE / Editors / OS
# ------------------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Python cache (common in the same directory as interop_runner.py)
# ------------------------------------------------------------
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Documentation / Non-build inputs (optional, to reduce context size)
# Note: If the Dockerfile needs documentation in the future, remember to uncomment this section
# ------------------------------------------------------------
docs/
*.md
!README.md

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Top-level directories not in the Dockerfile COPY list (to avoid accidentally entering the context)
# ------------------------------------------------------------
aiokafka_pkgs/
official-interop/

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Pruning of third-party subdirectories
#
# Note: boringssl's CMakeLists.txt unconditionally invokes add_executable(bssl ...)
# and add_executable(test_fips ...), which correspond to source files under tool/
# and util/fipstools/. Even if we do not build these targets, the cmake configure
# phase will scan whether the source files exist, and will fail if they are missing.
# Therefore, tool/, util/fipstools/, and crypto/*/test/ CANNOT be excluded
# and must enter the context along with the source code.
#
# fuzz/ does not seem to be unconditionally referenced by add_executable currently,
# so it can be safely excluded; if a future boringssl upgrade makes fuzz an
# unconditional target, simply comment out the line below.
# ------------------------------------------------------------
third/boringssl/fuzz/
third/googletest/docs/
